explanation: [0-0] A large duck with grey feathers and a black beak is in a pond. Green aquatic plants grow along the edge of the pond, and the water surface shimmers.

[0-7] The large duck paddles its feet, gliding through the water. It then uses its beak to pull at the feathers of a duckling near the water plants. Several other ducklings start swimming nearby. The large duck stretches its neck to eat the aquatic plants. At this moment, a large fish slowly approaches the duck flock from underwater. The fish continues swimming forward, startling the ducklings, who quickly swim towards the bank. The large duck stretches its beak to peck at the fish.
